msgstr "我想讀第三本屬於達夫拉尼德流亡者的日誌。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate fancy reading mode. Our civilization is one of the greatest examples of our race's pragmatism. We build magnificent structures, advanced technologies, weapons, armor based on inventions of our dedicated scientists and engineers. We must be proud, of our government, of us being superior to majority of other races, of us essentially monopolizing tech market in our and local galaxy systems.\n"
" \n"
"    Ways of conquering for us are via diplomacy, money, financial enslavements, dependency of others on us, this we use for our own advantage. Not really proud to work with a bunch of space pirates, Arganoides, neither with blood craving, killing for sport or whatever savages, Saldeniums. However, Davranides...are obsessed with their genetical splicing and deep science...we must not tread on them, be allies, but keep an eye on them obviously"
msgstr ""
"啟動華麗閱讀模式。我們的文明是我們種族實用主義的偉大典範之一。我們建造宏偉的建築、先進的技術、武器和裝甲，這些都基於我們敬業的科學家和工程師的發明。我們必須感到自豪，為我們的政府，為我們優於大多數其他種族，為我們基本壟斷了我們及鄰近星系系統的科技市場。\n"
"\n"
"我們的征服方式是通過外交、金錢、金融奴役、他人對我們的依賴，這些我們都用來為自己謀利。與一群太空海盜阿爾加諾伊德合作並不光彩，也不與嗜血、以殺戮為樂或任何野蠻的薩爾代尼姆人為伍。然而，達夫拉尼德人……痴迷於他們的基因拼接和深奧科學……我們絕不能與他們為敵，要結盟，但顯然要提防他們。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate fancy reading mode. We change as we advance. In terms of our technological advancements, no other race is match for us, but this turns us into cruel, devious, calculating tyrants slowly. We've monopolized tech markets successfully in our, also in local galaxy systems. We've grown proud of ourselves so much that conquered races are shunned upon by our native citizens, exploited by local companies as slaves.\n"
" \n"
"    This entire attempt to seize BL9 on a ravaged planet, killing everyone on sight including humans, proves my point. We've formed an 'Alliance' with 'adventurers' or pirates, Arganoides. We deal with violent wars waging warriors and mercenaries, Saldeniums. Though, Davranides are the most shady of them all. I've never seen a race so obsessed with genetical splicing or mutations, I've heard stories of how tyrannical their superiors are, 'directing' all of their citizens according to their own world view as well"
msgstr ""
"啟動華麗閱讀模式。我們隨著進步而改變。在技術進步方面，沒有其他種族能與我們匹敵，但這使我們逐漸變成殘忍、狡詐、精於算計的暴君。我們成功壟斷了我們及鄰近星系系統的科技市場。我們變得如此自傲，以至於被征服的種族遭到我們本土公民的排斥，被當地公司當作奴隸剝削。\n"
"\n"
"這次在滿目瘡痍的星球上奪取BL9、見人就殺（包括人類）的整個行動，證明了我的觀點。我們與‘冒險家’或海盜阿爾加諾伊德結成了‘聯盟’。我們與好戰的戰士和傭兵薩爾代尼姆人打交道。不過，達夫拉尼德人是其中最可疑的。我從未見過一個種族如此痴迷於基因拼接或突變，我聽說過他們的上級是多麼暴虐，如何按照自己的世界觀‘指導’所有公民。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate fancy reading mode. We all contribute to our society's advancing. Genetical splicing of microorganisms, creation of mutagens along with drugs based on their properties, lots of work on peculiar ones, such as symbiotes, we excel at all of this. Our society does it's best to 'direct' our own people to the right way, even if it means prohibitions or strict rules to abide by for our own citizens. Some fools even say, 'exploiting' or simply 'experimenting on' inferior races, it's for their own good, it's for our own society's good.\n"
" \n"
"    Our government, our diligently working scientists, researchers, subjects, all work for the sake of Davranides' future of all of us united with no traces of opposition between us. With BL9, a unique, flexible, powerful symbiote, we will be able to alter our own race genetically to be the dominant race across hundreds of galaxies. Calculating Wanzeltiums with other races all across galaxies depending on them will be our mere slaves when we use BL9 to advance our race as well"
msgstr ""
"啟動華麗閱讀模式。我們都為我們社會的進步貢獻力量。微生物的基因拼接、基於其特性的誘變劑和藥物的創造、對特殊生物（如共生體）的大量研究，我們都擅長這一切。我們的社會盡力‘引導’我們的人民走向正確的道路，即使這意味著對我們自己的公民實施禁令或嚴格規定。有些傻瓜甚至說，‘剝削’或僅僅‘在劣等種族身上做實驗’，是為了他們好，也是為了我們社會的好。\n"
"\n"
"我們的政府、我們勤奮工作的科學家、研究員、實驗對象，所有人都在為達夫拉尼德的未來而努力，讓我們所有人團結一致，沒有一絲反對的痕跡。藉助BL9這種獨特、靈活、強大的共生體，我們將能夠從基因上改造我們的種族，成為數百個星系中的主導種族。精於算計的萬澤爾提姆人以及其他依賴他們的星系種族，當我們使用BL9來提升我們的種族時，都將成為我們的奴隸。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate fancy reading mode. Usually we are not interested in projects of these savages. Majority of them are either mindless mutants, used for killing, or power hungry fools, obsessed with domination of local areas. They don't even care about improving living conditions for their own people. However, there are a few human scientists, who have told me about their most experienced scientist. It is the leader of 'True Superiors' organization at the same time essentially. Humans are feeble, mostly are worthless. But not this man. Even I, representative of a superior race, fear this man. It's like he is not even a man at this point. So what they said is that on their Militarized Island, with instructions made by this man, they developed a Super Soldier.\n"
" \n"
"    I came to Militarized Island to see quality of their work. It was pretty good, still, lacking many features that we could add. It was obviously a carefully made humanoid amalgamation of mutated animals that each of our 'Alliance' races brought here. Later when I wanted to talk with these scientists about our own, Davranides' projects, they told me that this man knows that I was one of the few Davranides scientists who showed interest in Super Soldier Project. Scientists said that this man insists that we enhance this project further. I said that I am not sure, but scientists simply replied. They said that Davranides will take on this work if 'Alliance' as a whole values their safety on Earth essentially. We don't want to make enemies out of our allies. We continued this project ourselves. Enhanced versions can be found in various impact sites Cave Systems, whereas experimental enhanced versions can be found in our own Mobile Bases"
msgstr ""
"啟動華麗閱讀模式。通常我們對這些野蠻人的項目不感興趣。他們大多數要麼是無腦的突變體，用於殺戮，要麼是權力飢渴的傻瓜，痴迷於統治局部地區。他們甚至不關心改善自己人民的生活條件。然而，有幾位人類科學家告訴我他們最有經驗的科學家。他同時也是‘真正至上’組織的領袖。人類是脆弱的，大多毫無價值。但這個人不同。即使是我，一個優越種族的代表，也畏懼這個人。他此刻簡直不像人類。他們說的是，在他們的軍事化島嶼上，按照這個人的指示，他們開發了一個超級士兵。\n"
"\n"
"我來到軍事化島嶼查看他們工作的質量。相當不錯，但仍然缺乏許多我們可以添加的功能。這顯然是一個精心製作的人形融合體，由我們‘聯盟’各個種族帶來的突變動物組成。後來，當我想與這些科學家討論我們達夫拉尼德自己的項目時，他們告訴我，這個人知道我是少數對超級士兵項目感興趣的達夫拉尼德科學家之一。科學家們說，這個人堅持要求我們進一步強化這個項目。我說我不確定，但科學家們只是回答。他們說，如果‘聯盟’整體重視他們在地球上的安全，達夫拉尼德將接手這項工作。我們不想與盟友為敵。我們自己繼續了這個項目。強化版本可以在各種撞擊點的洞穴系統中找到，而實驗性強化版本可以在我們自己的移動基地中找到。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate fancy reading mode. I've grown without father, like majority of Davranides families. We breed or 'fuck', they feed us a drug that cleanses love, affection hormones, amplifying pleasure hormones. Simply no love or affection allowed, it confuses minds they say. A bright child, I've got education in a prestigious university, worked in one of our top symbiotes research centers. I've learned a lot from our female mentor, she has shown me her personal projects, hidden from authorities, beneficial drugs, not just symbiote weapons. One of them restores all of our hormones to normal levels. We've developed forbidden affection, love, got lost in it but we were happy.\n"
" \n"
"    One of our authorities suspects 'unsanctioned experiments', frames my mentor, she gets killed, my own people destroy all of trust I had for them. Years after, I'm an experienced scientist. This fucktard confronts me, tells me I should be grateful he didn't frame me. I tell him all I think about him. We fight, he forcefully injects me with an experimental symbiote. I brutally smash fuckard into a pulp with my tentacle hammers. I escape via 'Alliance' portal to Earth, then I disguise as a human, I try to help a friendly organization to rebuild. Search for love, tell 'fuck off' to everyone else who prevents you from doing so. Find him or her. Be happy. I still search for my love with hope as well"
msgstr ""
"啟動華麗閱讀模式。我和大多數達夫拉尼德家庭一樣，在沒有父親的環境中長大。我們繁殖或‘交配’，他們給我們喂一種藥物，清除愛和情感激素，放大快感激素。簡單來說，不允許愛或情感，他們說這會擾亂心智。作為一個聰明的孩子，我在一所著名大學接受教育，在我們頂級的共生體研究中心工作。我從我們的女導師那裡學到了很多，她向我展示了她的個人項目，這些項目對當局隱瞞，是有益的藥物，不僅僅是共生體武器。其中一種能讓我們所有的激素恢復到正常水平。我們發展出了禁忌的情感、愛，迷失其中，但我們很快樂。\n"
"\n"
"我們的一位當局懷疑‘未經批准的實驗’，陷害了我的導師，她被殺害，我的人民摧毀了我對他們所有的信任。多年後，我成為一名經驗豐富的科學家。這個混蛋面對我，告訴我我應該感激他沒有陷害我。我告訴他我對他的所有看法。我們打鬥，他強行給我注射了一種實驗性共生體。我用我的觸手錘殘忍地將這個混蛋砸成肉醬。我通過‘聯盟’傳送門逃到地球，然後偽裝成人類，試圖幫助一個友好的組織重建。尋找愛，對任何阻止你這樣做的人說‘滾開’。找到他或她。要快樂。我仍然懷著希望尋找我的愛。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate fancy reading mode. I honestly try to not hide valuable info from my colleagues, but only 3 people: Subject5, Ulysses, I know about this. Just can't trust everyone, I'm essentially an exile to my own race, yet also one of the alien invaders to humans. Wanzeltiums with me have developed a unique technology: Energy Shield Generators that create a gigantic energy field based on sources that we've found on our planets. This field can protect people from horrors of Cataclysm, keeping even 'Alliance' militia away, shields are this strong.\n"
" \n"
"    Luckily, I've stolen blueprints, with me being responsible for most of this technology, they won't be able to replicate it any time soon. Still, version that I have built lacks generator amplifiers. This shield will only protect us if we install all of these amplifiers to my experimental Shield Generator. Not even mentioning need to salvage more of their tech to get more power cells to make multiple Shield Generators. If Ulysses' child, Subject5, is clever enough with putting intel or journals, armed survivors may help us to cleanse all of these areas that I've marked on this map in exactly this order. We lack military, we're trying to repel 'THEIR' attacks as much as we can, we clearly need help from survivors as well"
msgstr ""
"啟動華麗閱讀模式。我誠實地嘗試不向同事隱瞞有價值的信息，但只有三個人：Subject5、Ulysses，我知道這件事。只是不能信任所有人，我本質上是我自己種族的流亡者，同時也是人類的外星入侵者之一。與我一起的萬澤爾提姆人開發了一種獨特的技術：能量護盾發生器，它能基於我們在自己星球上發現的能源創造一個巨大的能量場。這個場可以保護人們免受大災變的恐怖，甚至能將‘聯盟’民兵擋在外面，護盾如此強大。\n"
"\n"
"幸運的是，我偷走了藍圖，由於我對這項技術的大部分負責，他們短期內無法複製。不過，我建造的版本缺少發生器放大器。只有當我們將所有放大器安裝到我的實驗性護盾發生器上，這個護盾才能保護我們。更不用說需要回收更多他們的技術來獲得更多能量電池，以製造多個護盾發生器。如果Ulysses的孩子Subject5足夠聰明，能夠放置情報或日誌，武裝倖存者可能會幫助我們按照地圖上標記的順序清理所有這些區域。我們缺乏軍事力量，我們盡力擊退‘他們’的攻擊，顯然我們也需要倖存者的幫助。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid ""
"Initiate joking mode. Got a selection of good things to read, stranger!"
msgstr "啟動玩笑模式。陌生人，這裡有些好東西可讀！"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid "Let's read Military Partners first journal"
msgstr "讓我們先讀軍事夥伴的第一本日誌。"

#: .\NPC\BL9_Base_Android.json
msgid "Let's read Military Partners second journal"
msgstr "讓我們讀軍事夥伴的第二本日誌。"

